**Segments**

- Based on treatment type, the malignant melanoma treatment market can be segmented into immunotherapy, targeted therapy, chemotherapy, radiation therapy, and surgical treatment. Immunotherapy, which includes immune checkpoint inhibitors and interleukin-2 therapies, is gaining prominence due to its ability to boost the body's immune system to fight cancer cells effectively. Targeted therapy focuses on specific genetic mutations in cancer cells to inhibit their growth. Chemotherapy involves the use of drugs to kill cancer cells, while radiation therapy uses high-energy beams to destroy cancer cells. Surgical treatment involves the removal of the tumor and surrounding tissues.

- By end user, the market can be categorized into hospitals, specialty clinics, cancer research institutes, and ambulatory surgical centers. Hospitals serve as a primary point of care for patients undergoing cancer treatment, providing comprehensive services from diagnosis to follow-up care. Specialty clinics often focus on specific types of cancer, offering specialized treatment options and expert care. Cancer research institutes play a vital role in advancing treatment modalities through clinical trials and research studies. Ambulatory surgical centers provide outpatient surgical procedures for cancer patients.

**Market Players**

- Some of the key players in the malignant melanoma treatment market include Bristol-Myers Squibb Company, Merck & Co., Inc., Amgen Inc., Novartis AG, Roche Holding AG, Pfizer Inc., AstraZeneca, Daiichi Sankyo Company, Limited, Sanofi, and AbbVie Inc. These companies are actively involved in research and development initiatives to introduce innovative treatment options for malignant melanoma. Collaborations, partnerships, and acquisitions are common strategies employed by market players to expand their product portfolios and geographical presence. Additionally, advancements in precision medicine and personalized treatment approaches are driving the market towards more effective and targeted therapies.

